><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=63.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ROD LOCATIONS, and HINTS...</span><hr size=1> First off get a few Waterstones summoned by a Mage, and collect Batwings for Levitation...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    1. Azia- Erud's crossing</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Use Waterstone, and cast Levitation....after that invis up, and float to the location <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    -1162 +2340</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, now start diving to the ground, and you'll see the Rod glowing, grab it, and gate after that...(btw... i saw no sharks here)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    2. Beza- Everfrost</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
The Hole in the Ice is located at <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    +2420 -4060</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->... find it, use a Waterstone, jump in, and swim North til u hit the Cave...enter the Cave and run along the right wall til you find the House at <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    +5000 -5092</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->... The Rod is located IN the House, and guarded by 3 iceboned skeletts...<br>
A different danger i saw with this rod was, a Red Con (at lvl.35 and scowling) Skelett crossed my way (name <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=3558">'Lich of Miragul'</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->) and it see thru invis... i was able to make a circle around it, keep eyes open for it...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    3. Caza- Lake Rathe</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Enter Lake Rathe from SK or RM.... use levitate, waterstone, and invis...float over the water to the Loc <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    +2800 -901</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, at this point start diving... there is a big Hole, swim in it... always straight til you reach the tower at location <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    +2785 +130</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->... the rod is in the tower, grab it (invis shoudn't drop) swim away, and gate out... nothing agroed me<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    4. Dena- Dagnor's Cauldron</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Easy Pie... enter Dagnor's Cauldron... Levitate / Invis up.... float to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    -890 -740</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, start diving and grab the rod... i saw no mobs nearby <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    5. Ena- Lower Guk</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
IMHO the hardest part of the Quest...<br>
I had a friend to help me with this, otherwise i woudn't be able to solve this <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
Enter lguk, ask for IvU from a cleric or chanter...make your way to the hand room, and ask someone to train the hand and frog to zone (or get hand/frog killed by someone), while he does that swim up, and grab the rod, and gate out...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    6. Fana- Oasis</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Easy again....use Waterstone / Invis...go near the Spectre Island to the Water, and dive to the loc <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    -786 -64</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, there is a tower located 'under' water where the rod can be found... the goblins there shoudn't agro when invis is up, and invis won't drop when you pick the rod up...easy<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    7. Geza- Highpass</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Located at <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    -218 +435</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> easy to find... keep invis up when you play a Darkelf, otherwise you could get jumped...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    8. Heda- Qeynos Aqueducts</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Located at No#14 on this Map here : <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eqatlas.com/qeynoscatacombsmap.html">eqatlas.com/qeynoscatacombsmap.html</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    9. Izah- Neriak</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Located in the Water near <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    +8 -807</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> in 'Neriak Commons' ... easy to find <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    10. Jaka- Unrest</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Enter Unrest, run til you see the House, go right... there is water, jump in, and stay on the right wall... its a little hidden corner where the rod is....loc is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    +520 -290</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
After you got all Rods go back to Everfrost to Location <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    +3033 -2393</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> where the Quest NPC can be found (Sulgar), hail him, ask for the chest, stick all rods inside, combine... and get Staff of the Wheel, and Star of Eyes...<br>
Give Staff of Wheel + Star of Eyes to Sulgar to get the Icecomet spell runes...<br>
<br>
Good Luck with this Quest <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
