<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=132459>Daamij</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uxildarie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xildarie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/26/02 9:06:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=63.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re ROD LOCATIONS , and HINTS...</span><hr size=1> I tested the DW goblins with a friends 51 druid, only SOME see thru invis, i am guessing this is the wizard type ones, seeing as how i started getting hit with some hard hitting fed flasshy stuff that seemed to me to be like a spell my wizzy has...i suck at spell names but once one agros they all do, conn em all and if one sees thru invis you will have to get someone to pullem i guess <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucallissagatecaller.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Callissa Gatecaller</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/27/02 4:55:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=63.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re ROD LOCATIONS , and HINTS...</span><hr size=1> It is not only the caster goblins that can see invis. Basically, any caster goblin can cast see invis upon himself and other mobs in range, and will do so after a short time after spawn.<br>
<br>
The goblins do not aggro on wolf form though, neither in Oasis nor in Lake Rathetear. <p><B><I><font color="silver"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=65423" target="_new">Callissa Gatecaller</a><BR>
