</CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=vithrilsathir>Vithril Sathir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/3/02 11:25:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=63.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ROD LOCATIONS, and HINTS...</span><hr size=1> My first post on Graffe's, wohoo!  I feel I must reply to this thread to thank Deewee for the awesome info for the Staff of the Wheel quest.  I highly recommend printing out the rod locations and hints provided.  I can confirm that this can be done solo at L30 except for maybe LGuk.  Last night I took the liberty of printing out Deewee's info along with printing out the Qeynos catacomb map and LGuk maps from EQAtlas.  I had no problems except I did need a more detailed explaination of where to look in Erud's crossing.  If it helps, you get off the boat when riding from Qeynos to Odus.  The boat will stop at a Island with a few Cat people.  Get off and run to the opposite side of the island.  There, just offshore you will see a sunken ship with its mast sticking out of the water.  The rod is to the right of the mast and just a bit beyond the ship.  I have 9 out of 10 rods now and just have to find a few high levels willing to help escort me to LGuk for my final rod in guk.  Thanks again for the great info in this forum concerning the Staff of the Wheel and long live Graffe's website!<br>
